19/04/2005
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Johan Tarculovski, 30, a Macedonian police officer, pleaded not guilty to charges of murder and cruel treatment of detainees, during an appearance before the UN tribunal in The Hague on Monday (18 April). He led a special police unit that raided the village of Ljuboten near Skopje in August 2001. Several ethnic Albanian residents were killed during the operation.
In other news, Vujadin Popovic, a former Bosnian Serb army officer, appeared before the UN court on Monday to plead not guilty to charges of genocide and crimes against humanity. He served with the Drina Corps, which was responsible for most of the executions of Muslims in Srebrenica in July 1995. (Reuters, AFP, Fena, PBS BiH - 18/04/05)
